s a blow from which, arguably, the Byzantines never fully recovered.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Jul 2022) 0aByzantine literaturexCriticism, Textual. 0aDialoguexSocial aspectszByzantine EmpirexHistory. 0aDiscourse analysiszByzantine Empire. 0aDiscussionxSocial aspectszByzantine EmpirexHistory. 7aHISTORY / Medieval.2bisacsh  a12th century, Byzantium, Greece, Jews, Muslims.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertCentral European University Press eBook-Package 2016z978311078053640uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9789633861127423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9789633861127/original  a978-3-11-078053-6  Central European University Press eBook-Package 2016b2016  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_HICS  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_HICS  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA13ENGE  aPDA17SSHEE  aPDA5EBK